        Tour Intro — “Berlin Wall & Cold War”

Welcome to a city once divided.

For nearly three decades, a concrete wall split Berlin in two — separating families, friends, and an entire world of ideas.

On this tour, you’ll walk the line that once divided East from West, discovering stories of courage, escape, and the human will to be free.

From the solemn silence of Bernauer Straße to the bright lights of Potsdamer Platz, each stop reveals how Berliners lived, resisted, and ultimately tore down the Wall that defined their lives.

This is not just history — it’s a story of resilience, hope, and reunification.
